id: pmc-pr0j
title: Harden release bun-verify so registry-mirror lag cannot block the GitHub release
description: Make the Daily Release resilient to bun registry-mirror lag so a cosmetic verify failure never blocks the actual GitHub release.
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[2]: ci,release-readiness
created_at: "2026-06-13T22:24:23.717Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-18T09:55:50.833Z"
deadline: "2026-06-15T00:00:00.000Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-18T09:55:50.832Z"
author: claude
estimated_minutes: 45
acceptance_criteria: "bun-verify retries 8x then falls back to authoritative 'npm view pkg@version'; npm-confirmed publishes emit ::warning:: and exit 0 so Create GitHub release runs; only a genuinely-absent npm version fails the job; release:check+test pass; no secrets."
resolution: release.yml verify step falls back to authoritative npm view after bun-verify retries
expected_result: release.yml verify step exits 0 on npm-confirmed publishes despite bun mirror lag; GitHub release is created.
actual_result: Fallback shipped fleet-wide 2026-06-14; Daily Releases green since (verified 2026-07-18)
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pmc-8ssd,related,"2026-06-13T22:24:23.717Z",claude,null
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-13T22:24:23.717Z",claude,Lead repo for the fleet-wide fix; identical release.yml verify block exists in all active pm repos.
  "2026-07-18T09:55:17.581Z",pi-agent,"Verified done 2026-07-18: .github/workflows/release.yml contains the npm-authoritative fallback (npm view fallback after bun-verify retries). This repo was the origin of the fix (pm-changelog#49), propagated fleet-wide 2026-06-14; multiple successful Daily Releases since (latest July 2026). Acceptance criteria met."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-13T22:24:23.717Z",claude,pm-changelog 2026.6.13-1 GitHub release was missing and backfilled manually before this fix.
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-13T22:24:23.717Z",claude,"Calendar -N suffixes are semver prereleases; bun resolves prerelease specifiers via a mirror that lags npm publish,so the verify smoke test is the flakiest for -N releases."
files[1]{path,scope,note}:
  .github/workflows/release.yml,project,verify step + ordering
tests[1]{command,scope,timeout_seconds}:
  "npm run release:check",project,300
docs[1]{path,scope,note}:
  .github/workflows/release.yml,project,release workflow being hardened
close_reason: npm-authoritative bun-verify fallback shipped; acceptance criteria met
body: "The 'Verify bun install of published package' step is fatal (exit 1 after 5x30s) and ordered before 'Create GitHub release'. bun's registry mirror can lag past that 2.5-min window, worst for prerelease (-N) versions, even after npm publish + git tag + changelog commit succeed. This blocked pm-changelog 2026.6.13-1's GitHub release. Fix adds an npm-authoritative fallback."
